What is Massage Chair Controller?
A Massage Chair Controller is an embedded electronic system that orchestrates the mechanical and therapeutic functions of a massage chair. It typically comprises a microcontroller or System‑on‑Chip (SoC), power management circuitry, motor drivers, temperature regulation modules, and a user interface layer (touch panel, remote, or mobile app). Advanced controllers also embed pressure‑sensing mats, biometric sensors, Bluetooth Low Energy, Wi‑Fi, and cloud‑connected firmware to enable AI‑driven personalization and over‑the‑air updates.

